Johannesburg - Joburg City Power has blamed the constant and persistent power outages in northern Johannesburg on cable   faults, burnt switches and stolen ring main units. The power outages have been experienced in parts of Randburg and some surrounding areas. Joburg City Power has blamed the outages on cable faults, burnt switches and stolen ring main units. Joburg City Power teams have been hard at work trying to resolve the problems and to restore the power in these areas. Various areas in and around Olievenhout were affected such as: Northwold Northriding Bellairs Drive Honeydew Boskop Business Park Zandspruit Sundowner Sonneglans The power utility says repairs in these areas have been completed on Thursday and power would be restored once the load reduces. Surrounding areas such as Blairgowrie and Bryanston were also impacted due to a burnt switch and stolen ring main unit in the areas. Repairs are still under way. City Power has assured all customers that the teams will work tirelessly to resolve the matters and will communicate any changes. But it appeared the outages in the northern regions were persisting. #OutageUpdate on Block 14. ^NN pic.twitter.com/MHlUTUXgYp #OutageUpdate on Randburg .^NN pic.twitter.com/dsgw2TwW7l #OutageUpdate on Hursthill  .^NN pic.twitter.com/YxYPAeVJjD  #OutageUpdate on Randburg .^NN pic.twitter.com/eMKxfXOi3K Joburg City Power has apologised to the fuming affected residents who have been flooding them on social media with complaints. Are we actually having load shedding Stage 11 and you just didn't want to tell us? Why is the power out in Block 8, Sundowner again???????ü§¶üèΩ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è pic.twitter.com/ocX1supI0Q  Its been 50 hours of no electricity.  Was this not one of the reasons you gave during our hours of blackouts? How are we back to this again? So cables replaced, cables stolen ü§îwhat the hell? Where was this cables stolen? We want proof that teams are working on this.  Firstly go grab some coffee to wake up. It‚Äôs da